{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778185700,"nonce":"ILjIuYCH/weKe47LZ3ID7Ih0DYk=","message":"**Audit findings — old-feedbax-API references in rlrmp**\n\nPerformed a sweep across `src/rlrmp/`, `scripts/`, `tests/` for old staged-model API references: `Iterator`, `AbstractStagedModel`, `AbstractIterator`, `ModelInput`, `model.step`, `AbstractIntervenor`, `feedbax.iterations`, `feedbax.staged`, `staged.py`. Verdict per site:\n\n**Genuinely broken — fixed in this branch:**\n- `scripts/eval_part2_5.py:127` — `model.step.net.hidden.cell.weight_hh.shape[0]` accessing old staged-model path. Fixed to `model.net.hidden.cell.weight_hh.shape[0]` (graph attribute access on `SimpleFeedback`).\n- `scripts/eval_part2_5.py:174` — same pattern. Fixed.\n\n**Stale framing in docstrings — clarified:**\n- `src/rlrmp/analysis/hinf_riccati.py:linearize_from_model` docstring + ValueError message + `_walk_model_for_plant_params` inline comment referenced `Iterator wrapping SimpleFeedback`. Under develop's eager-graph cutover, `Iterator` is gone; `SimpleFeedback` is itself a `Graph` that runs cycles internally. Updated to drop `Iterator` references; tree-walking code itself was already fine.\n\n**Already correct — false positive:**\n- `src/rlrmp/intervention_compat.py` — already uses graph API (`from feedbax.graph import Wire`, `insert_between`, `add_wire`, `input_bindings`, `output_bindings`). The `SimpleFeedback` mentions in comments are just naming, not staged-API usage.\n- `src/rlrmp/disturbance.py`, `src/rlrmp/disturbances.py`, `src/rlrmp/adversarial_training.py` — use `feedbax.intervene.TimeSeriesParam` etc., which exist on develop.\n- `src/rlrmp/loss.py`, `src/rlrmp/task.py`, `src/rlrmp/viz/loss_viz.py`, `src/rlrmp/modules/training/part2.py`, `src/rlrmp/modules/analysis/part2/{fps_steady,unit_perts}.py`, `scripts/train_minimax.py`, `tests/todo/test_{viz_modes,loss_viz}.py` — `from feedbax.task import …` and `from feedbax.task import TaskTrialSpec` etc. `feedbax.task` is still a valid module on develop.\n- `src/rlrmp/modules/analysis/part2/fps_steady.py:479` — `model.step.net.readout.weight` is in commented-out code only. Left as-is.\n\n**No matches found:**\n- `feedbax.iterations`, `feedbax.staged`, `AbstractStagedModel`, `AbstractIterator`, `ModelInput`, `AbstractIntervenor` — clean. The architecture migration was already partially done in earlier rlrmp work; only two literal `model.step.` accesses (and stale docstring framing) remained.\n\nThe `feedbax_rnn_controller` adapter in `src/rlrmp/analysis/induced_gain.py` was not technically broken (no caller had wired up a real model yet), but it implicitly assumed the old API and the issue body specified replacing it. Replaced with `feedbax_graph_controller(graph, *, key)` that wraps a `Graph` directly via `_call_single_step` and flattens `State` to a 1D array for the analyser's existing Array-typed protocol. Smoke-tested with a minimal pass-through Graph (`tests/test_induced_gain.py::test_feedbax_graph_controller_smoke`); the legacy `feedbax_rnn_controller(step_fn, h0)` now raises `NotImplementedError` with a migration message.\n\nAll fixes are scoped to this branch (`feature/methodology-fix-followups`). No follow-up issues filed — every broken site was small enough to fix in-place.","files":null}]}